TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Find all solutions of the equation \( \cos x (2\sin x + 1) = 0. \)
$BR
The answer is \(A+k\pi\), \(B+2k\pi\) and \(C+2k\pi\) 
where \(k\) is any integer and \(0<A<\pi\), \(0<B<C<2\pi\),
$BR
\( A= \) \{ans_rule(15)\},
$BR
\( B= \) \{ans_rule(15)\},
$BR
\( C= \) \{ans_rule(15)\}.
$BR
EOT

$ans1= $PI/2;
$ans2= 7*$PI/6;
$ans3= 11*$PI/6;

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));

